div do
note <<-MARKDOWN
There are several ways of opening a command prompt window.  You'll be using it often, so the best way is creating an shortcut icon on the Taskbar. 

  MARKDOWN
  end

step "Opening a command prompt " do
  note <<-MARKDOWN

## Windows 7 
* Click the Windows Icon. In the "Search programs and files" field, type: <tt>cmd <enter></tt>
![Win7_search_programs.jpg](Win7_search_programs.jpg)

  MARKDOWN
  end

step "Creating a command prompt shortcut icon on the Taskbar " do
  note <<-MARKDOWN

## Windows 7 
* Click: Windows Icon, "All Programs", "Accessories". Right click on "Command Prompt", click on "Pin to Taskbar".
  MARKDOWN
end
